1 (5) For purposes of imposing the special assessment and
2 determining the benefits of the district's activities and
3 improvements, a classification of the types of businesses
4 within the proposed district. The classification may include
5 the following variations in the assessment formula:
6 (A) Square footage of the business.
7 (B) Number of employees.
8 (C) Geography.
9 (D) Gross sales.
10 (E) Other similar factors that reasonably relate to the
11 benefit received.
12 (6) An estimate of the amount of revenue needed to
13 accomplish or pay for the district's proposed activities and
14 improvements.
15 (7) Subject to section 9.5 of this chapter, a statement
16 identifying the district management association, including the
